abstract: Nine opposition parties in Liberia express dissatisfaction with presidential election, threatening to disavow result when it is announced; signals potential trouble in country with a history of political violence.
snippet: Parties in the running against President Ellen Johnson Sirleaf of Liberia threatened to disavow the result of the presidential election when it is announced.
lead_paragraph: Parties in the running against President Ellen Johnson Sirleaf of Liberia threatened to disavow the result of the presidential election when it is announced.

headline.main: Liberians Count Votes and Fraud Allegations
